== Soup ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced) into ¼-inch pieces. Halve
@celery{2.5%oz}(halved lengthwise and diced) lengthwise; dice into ¼-inch pieces.
Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}(drained and rinsed) and @kidney beans{1}(drained and rinsed). Roughly chop @parsley{¼%oz}(roughly chopped).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium heat. Add
onion, celery, @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll
use the rest in the next step), a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{} to taste. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and lightly browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

> If onion browns too quickly, add a splash of water and lower heat.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, @Israeli couscous{2.5%oz}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz}, half the cannellini beans,
half the kidney beans, 2 cups water, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

> Use all the cannellini and kidney beans and 4 cups water for 4 servings.

Increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a
low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans and couscous are tender,
~{10-15%minutes}.

== Garlicky Breadsticks ==

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1}(halved lengthwise) lengthwise; slice each
half lengthwise into thirds.

In a large #bowl{}, toss baguette pieces with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%tsp}, remaining garlic powder, and salt and pepper to taste until
evenly coated. Arrange seasoned baguette pieces on a #baking sheet{} and bake on
top rack until lightly toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove baking sheet from oven; carefully flip breadsticks and return to top rack
until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Divide soup between #bowls{}; garnish with parsley. Serve with breadsticks on
the side.